Made with Southern Star Bourbon, apple-spiced tea, winter spices, orange & lemon, and malted milk, this drink is a silky-smooth, well-balanced fusion of warmth and brightness. The spiced tea complements the bourbon’s richness, while the citrus elements add just the right amount of acidity. The clarification process gives it a clean, velvety texture, making it an effortlessly drinkable yet complex cocktail.
A Cozy, Elevated Experience—One of the standout aspects of Chiefs is its very cool vibe—a perfect balance of sophistication and comfort. Sitting by the fireplace in four club chairs, the experience felt both intimate and effortlessly stylish. The setting created an atmosphere that was warm, relaxed, and inviting, making it ideal for both a casual evening and a refined night out.

reviews_data.review_text: Well I've been waiting for someone to break the $16 barrier for cocktails in our area and unfortunately the drinks, service and atmosphere don't warrant $19 for a run of the mill drink. I ordered the cynar boulevardier off the classic menu. It was ok. Nothing special and not anything I couldn't also get at any other bar in noda/villa/optimist for $14. Cynar isn't special anymore, and not to sound like a jerk which I'm sure I do, hasn't been special for a decade now. Also it's made with mid level 1792 bourbon and mid level vermouth so really just feels like a big swing and miss price wise. My wife got a drink off the special menu and the mix of "popcorn and sherry"  just didn't work for either of us. I hate being negative to a local business, but the prices are way out of alignment with the service and atmosphere. It's not that the service/atmosphere was bad, but to charge $19 for a drink, you need to differentiate yourself from all nearby competitors. I better leave feeling impressed by everything and this time I didn't. We ate no food on our visit, just decided to go to growlers instead after the two drinks just didn't leave us wanting anymore.

The spiced tea complements the bourbon’s richness, while the citrus elements add just the right amount of acidity. The clarification process gives it a clean, velvety texture, making it an effortlessly drinkable yet complex cocktail.
A Cozy, Elevated Experience—One of the standout aspects of Chiefs is its very cool vibe—a perfect balance of sophistication and comfort. Sitting by the fireplace in four club chairs, the experience felt both intimate and effortlessly stylish. The setting created an atmosphere that was warm, relaxed, and inviting, making it ideal for both a casual evening and a refined night out.

reviews_data.review_text: Well I've been waiting for someone to break the $16 barrier for cocktails in our area and unfortunately the drinks, service and atmosphere don't warrant $19 for a run of the mill drink. I ordered the cynar boulevardier off the classic menu. It was ok. Nothing special and not anything I couldn't also get at any other bar in noda/villa/optimist for $14. Cynar isn't special anymore, and not to sound like a jerk which I'm sure I do, hasn't been special for a decade now. Also it's made with mid level 1792 bourbon and mid level vermouth so really just feels like a big swing and miss price wise. My wife got a drink off the special menu and the mix of "popcorn and sherry"  just didn't work for either of us. I hate being negative to a local business, but the prices are way out of alignment with the service and atmosphere. It's not that the service/atmosphere was bad, but to charge $19 for a drink, you need to differentiate yourself from all nearby competitors. I better leave feeling impressed by everything and this time I didn't. We ate no food on our visit, just decided to go to growlers instead after the two drinks just didn't leave us wanting anymore.

We understand that pricing is a big factor, and we take great care in crafting our cocktails with carefully selected spirits and ingredients. That said, we never want a guest to leave feeling underwhelmed, and we’ll take your feedback into account as we continue refining our menu and overall experience.

We’d love the chance to welcome you back in the future and hopefully change your mind. If you ever decide to give us another shot, please don’t hesitate to reach out—we’d be happy to make it right.

Cheers,
The Management Team at Chiefs

reviews_data.review_text: Chief’s offers a lovely atmosphere, attentive service and exceptional drinks - Bob is a master mixologist! We enjoyed hearing from him about the clarifying process that produced the Rise and Grind cocktail I had which tasted like a creamy espresso martini, but was actually coffee infused clear whisky! The clarified malted milk punch was also clear and had an aroma of a spiced apple cider and was delicious. The Pisco Sour had a rich, thick and creamy bergamot foam on the top that was so tasty! We sat in front of the fire on a cold February evening enjoying drinks and the toasted focaccia. Other patrons were friendly and conversational, our server Jackie was patient, friendly and so helpful and I hugged Bob when I left knowing confidently I would be back. If you’re looking for unique and tasty drinks coupled with a warm friendly atmosphere, check out Chief’s- guarantee you love it!
reviews_data.owner_answer:

It’s wonderful that you felt welcomed by both our team and fellow patrons, and we love that you got to cozy up by the fire with some delicious drinks and toasted focaccia. Jacque will be so happy to hear your kind words, and we’ll be sure to pass along your appreciation to her and Bob.

We can’t wait to welcome you back for more unique and tasty drinks in our warm, friendly atmosphere. Until next time.

Cheers! 
-The Management Team at Chiefs

reviews_data.review_text: So glad that there is another craft cocktail bar joining the CLT scene—in NODA specifically. I have to say after my first visit to Chiefs I suspect they may be working a few things out still, having only recently opened. Firstly, the service is great, no complaints there. The bartenders are very knowledgeable and attentive. To offer some gentle feedback, the drinks were made with quality ingredients but were over diluted. This could have been a one off, but it was noticeable across different cocktails. The atmosphere is generally nice. There is a some seating by a fire place that seems absolutely lovely. Sitting at the bar though, I was distracted by the large flat screen TV. For me, it took me out of the cozy, craft cocktail bar experience. Finally, I do think the price point is maybe a bit too high compared to what other bars in the cocktail scene are offering. It has a lot of potential and I would give it another try in 6+ months.

We also really appreciate your constructive feedback. We’re continuously fine-tuning our cocktails, and we’ll be sure to take a closer look at dilution to ensure every drink is perfectly balanced. As for the atmosphere, we want to create a space that feels inviting to all, and your thoughts on the TV placement are noted. Pricing is always something we evaluate, and we’ll keep an eye on how we’re stacking up with the rest of the CLT cocktail scene.

We’d love to welcome you back in the future and hope to impress you even more next time. Thanks again for your support and for giving us a chance to grow—we truly appreciate it!

Cheers,
Management Team
